        <div n="235-06H1" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-235-06H1-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-235-06H1-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-235-06H1-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-235-06H1-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-235-06H1-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-235-06H1-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-235-06H1-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-235-06H1-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-235-06H1-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-235-06H1-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">B</hi>ENEATH this verdant <hi rend="underline">hillock</hi> lies<hi rend="underline">Demar</hi>, the <hi rend="underline">wealthy</hi> and the <hi rend="underline">wise</hi>.<gap/><gap/></l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-235-06H1-line-2"> His <hi rend="underline">heirs</hi>, that he might safely rest,</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-235-06H1-line-3"> Have put his <hi rend="underline">carcass</hi> in a <hi rend="underline">chest</hi>;</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-235-06H1-line-4"> The very <hi rend="underline">chest</hi>, in which, they say,</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-235-06H1-line-5"> His <hi rend="underline">other self</hi>, his <hi rend="underline">money</hi> lay.</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-235-06H1-line-6"> And, if his <hi rend="underline">heirs</hi> continue kind</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-235-06H1-line-7"> To that dear <hi rend="underline">self</hi> he left behind,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-235-06H1-line-8"> I dare believe, that four in five</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-235-06H1-line-9"> Will think his <hi rend="underline">better half</hi> alive.235-06H1   </l></lg></div>
